# Design System Rules

## Component Priority

1. `@vistral/design-system` — always prefer (Button, Input, Select, Dialog, Card, Tabs, etc.)
2. `@/components/ui/` — only for components not yet in Vistral DS
3. If creating locally, add comment: `// TODO: Candidate for Vistral DS`

Storybook: https://vistral-design-system.vercel.app/

## Design Tokens

CSS variables use `--vistral-*` prefix (preferred), with `--prophero-*` fallback.

- Colors: `--vistral-color-primary-500`, `--vistral-color-success/warning/error/info`, `--vistral-gray-*`
- Typography: `--vistral-font-size-sm` through `--vistral-font-size-header-3xl`, Inter font
- Spacing: `--vistral-spacing-0` through `--vistral-spacing-24`
- Radius: `--vistral-radius-1` (4px) through `--vistral-radius-6` (24px)
- Shadows: `--vistral-shadow-level-1` through `--vistral-shadow-level-4`

Token source: `@vistral/design-system/tokens.css` (imported in `app/globals.css`)

## Grid Breakpoints

| Breakpoint | Range | Margin | Gutter |
|------------|-------|--------|--------|
| XS | <576px | 20px | 12px |
| SM | 577-768px | 32px | 12px |
| MD | 769-992px | 40px | 16px |
| LG | 993-1199px | 80px | 28px |
| XL | 1200-1400px | 100px | 32px |
| XXL | >1400px | 112px centered max 1920px | 32px |

CSS classes: `container-margin`, `gutter`
TypeScript: `import { BREAKPOINTS, SPACING } from '@/lib/constants'`

## Component Patterns

- Always use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
- Use `cva()` + `VariantProps` for variant-based components
- Components wrapping native elements MUST use `forwardRef`
- Use Radix UI primitives for accessible modals, selects, dropdowns
- Dark mode via `.dark` class and CSS variables
